{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648923","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648923"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:59:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:59:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18335"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18335","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18335"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11053"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79186"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11053","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11053"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18335"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64538"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25642"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25644"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79186","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79186"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following changes is observed in the intervertebral discs during spondylosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Increase in water content","Decrease in water content","Increase in disc height","Increase in proteoglycan synthesis","Increase in disc elasticity"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESpondylosis refers to the degenerative changes in the spine, particularly affecting the intervertebral discs and vertebral bodies. These changes can lead to symptoms such as pain and reduced mobility.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn spondylosis, the intervertebral discs undergo degenerative changes, including a \u003Cstrong\u003Edecrease in water content\u003C/strong\u003E. This is due to alterations in proteoglycan metabolism, which reduces the disc\u0027s ability to retain water, leading to decreased disc height and elasticity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncrease in water content\u003C/strong\u003E - The water content decreases, not increases\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncrease in disc height\u003C/strong\u003E - Disc height decreases due to loss of water content\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncrease in proteoglycan synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E - Proteoglycan synthesis decreases, contributing to reduced water retention\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncrease in disc elasticity\u003C/strong\u003E - Disc elasticity decreases as a result of reduced water content\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Spondylosis is characterised by degenerative changes in the spine, including the intervertebral discs.","In spondylosis, there is a decrease in water content of the intervertebral discs.","Proteoglycan metabolism changes in spondylosis, leading to reduced disc hydration and elasticity."],"references":["Khurana, I., Khurana, A., \u0026 Kowlgi, N. G. (2019). Textbook of Medical Physiology_-E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Datta HK, Ng WF, Walker JA, Tuck SP, Varanasi SS. The cell biology of bone metabolism. J Clin Pathol. 2008 May;61(5):577-87. doi: 10.1136/jcp.2007.048868. PMID: 18441154","Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy